-- send_webhook.lua  (OpenComputers/OpenOS)
local internet = require("internet")
local component = require("component")
local computer = require("computer")
local io = require("io")

-- Replace with your webhook URL (keep this secret)
local webhook_url = "https://discord.com/api/webhooks/1431962412113727633/Vg0dWkp6Y94tmyXZAo_P_1LiLMuOJNWSbOcYQzwuyhA-fZps7BXdPtZGefSU2bIp1Oer"

-- Simple JSON escaper (handles quotes, backslashes and control chars)
local function json_escape(s)
  s = tostring(s)
  s = s:gsub("\\", "\\\\")
  s = s:gsub('"', '\\"')
  s = s:gsub("\b", "\\b")
  s = s:gsub("\f", "\\f")
  s = s:gsub("\n", "\\n")
  s = s:gsub("\r", "\\r")
  s = s:gsub("\t", "\\t")
  -- other control chars -> \u00XX
  s = s:gsub("([%z\1-\31])", function(c)
    return string.format("\\u%04x", string.byte(c))
  end)
  return s
end

-- Builds a minimal JSON payload for Discord webhook: { "username": "...", "content": "..." }
local function build_payload(username, content)
  username = username or "OC Bot"
  content = content or ""
  return string.format('{"username":"%s","content":"%s"}', json_escape(username), json_escape(content))
end

-- Post to webhook and return response body (or nil + error)
local function post_webhook(url, username, content)
  if not url then return nil, "no url provided" end
  local body = build_payload(username, content)
  local headers = {
    ["Content-Type"] = "application/json",
    ["Content-Length"] = tostring(#body),
    ["User-Agent"] = "OpenComputers-Webhook/1.0"
  }

  local ok, handle_or_err = pcall(internet.request, url, body, headers)
  if not ok or not handle_or_err then
    return nil, "request failed to start: " .. tostring(handle_or_err)
  end

  local handle = handle_or_err
  local resp = ""
  -- read the iterator returned by internet.request synchronously
  for chunk in handle do
    resp = resp .. tostring(chunk)
  end

  return resp
end

local f = io.open("/home/auth", "r")
local content = f:read("a")
f:close()

local resp, err = post_webhook(webhook_url, "OC server-1", "Login program started successfully. Boot auth status: ".. content)

if content == "False" then
    computer.shutdown("True")
end

local reactorName = "BiggerReactors_Reactor_1"
local maxTemp = 2000
local minTemp = 1000

local turbineName = "BiggerReactors_Turbine_0"
local targetRPM = 1800
local stepSize = 0.1

local checkInterval = 0.1
 
local mon = peripheral.wrap("monitor_2")
term.redirect(mon)
 
local reactor = peripheral.wrap(reactorName)
if not reactor then
  error("Reactor not found: " .. reactorName)
end
 
local turbine = peripheral.wrap(turbineName)
if not turbine then
  error("Turbine not found: " .. turbineName)
end
 
while true do
  local rodPercent = 100 * math.max(reactor.fuelTemperature() - minTemp, 0) / (maxTemp - minTemp)
  reactor.setAllControlRodLevels(rodPercent)
  
  local rpm = turbine.rotor().RPM()
  
  if rpm > targetRPM then
	turbine.fluidTank().setNominalFlowRate(turbine.fluidTank().nominalFlowRate() - stepSize)
  else
	turbine.fluidTank().setNominalFlowRate(turbine.fluidTank().nominalFlowRate() + stepSize)
  end  
  
  term.clear()
  term.setCursorPos(1,1)
  
  print("Temperature: " .. math.floor(reactor.fuelTemperature()))
  print("Rods: " .. math.floor(reactor.getControlRod(0).level()))
  sleep(checkInterval)
end

local RS = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")
local rebirth = RS:WaitForChild("RequestCompletionRebirth")

local maps = workspace.Maps
local mapId = 1
local found = maps and maps:FindFirstChild("Map"..mapId)
local burger = found and found.burger

local plr = game.Players.LocalPlayer

local stopped = false

local function re(h)
    if h then 
        h.Health = 0 
    end
end

plr.Chatted:Connect(function(msg)
    if msg == "StopInit" then 
        stopped = true 
    end
end)

while true do
    if stopped then 
        break 
    end
    local character = plr.Character or plr.CharacterAdded:Wait() 
    if character and burger then
        local humanoid = character:FindFirstChildOfClass("Humanoid") 
        character:PivotTo(burger:GetPivot())
        wait(0.5)
        local proximity = burger:FindFirstChild("ProximityPrompt")
        if proximity then
            proximity:InputHoldBegin()
            local triggered = false
            proximity.Triggered:Connect(function() 
                triggered = true 
            end)   
            local startTime = tick()
            while not triggered and (tick() - startTime) < 1 do
                wait(0.1)
            end
            if triggered then
                wait(1)
                rebirth:FireServer()
                wait(3)
            else
                re(humanoid)
                wait(5)
            end
        else
            re(humanoid)
            wait(5)
        end
    else
        re(humanoid)
        wait(5)
    end
end

import sys
from PIL import Image

def convert_to_grayscale_bmp(input_path, output_path):
    img = Image.open(input_path)
    grayscale_img = img.convert('L')
    grayscale_img.save(output_path, 'BMP')

input_file = sys.argv[1]
output_file = input_file.strip(".jpg") + ".bmp"

convert_to_grayscale_bmp(input_file, output_file)

title: Turbine control 2
content:
-- Peripheral setup
local modem = peripheral.find("modem") or error("No modem found", 0)
local monitor = peripheral.wrap("front") or error("No monitor on front", 0)

-- Monitor setup
monitor.setTextScale(0.5)
monitor.setBackgroundColor(colors.cyan)
monitor.clear()

local function drawLabel(y, text)
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, y)
    monitor.clearLine()
    monitor.write(text)
end

local function drawUI()
    drawLabel(4, "Fuel Feed")
    drawLabel(5, "-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-")
    drawLabel(8, "Clutch")
    drawLabel(9, "-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-")
    drawLabel(12, "Output")
    drawLabel(13, "-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-")
    monitor.setCursorPos(4, 1)
    monitor.write("Turbine #1")
end

drawUI()

term.clear()
term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
print("Running...")

-- Core Functions
local function transmitAndDisplay(channelOut, channelIn, mode, yPos, bgColor, side, pulse)
    if side then rs.setOutput(side, true) end
    modem.transmit(channelOut, channelIn, mode)
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, yPos)
    monitor.clearLine()
    monitor.blit(mode, ("0"):rep(#mode), bgColor)
    if pulse then sleep(1); if side then rs.setOutput(side, false) end end
end

local function fuelFeed(side, mode, bgColor)
    transmitAndDisplay(3, 4, mode, 6, bgColor, side, true)
end

local function shift(side, mode, bgColor)
    rs.setOutput("left", false)
    transmitAndDisplay(2, 3, mode, 10, bgColor, side, false)
end

local function modemCall(channel, callback)
    modem.open(channel)
    local _, _, _, _, message = os.pullEvent("modem_message")
    modem.close(channel)
    if callback then callback(message) end
    return message
end

local function battCall()
    return tonumber(modemCall(4, function(msg)
        term.setCursorPos(1, 2)
        term.clearLine()
        print(msg)
    end)) or 0
end

local function outputCall()
    modemCall(5, function(msg)
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, 14)
        monitor.clearLine()
        monitor.write(msg)
    end)
end

-- Main control loop
local inject, delay = 0, 0

while not rs.getInput("front") do
    local batt = battCall()
    local speed = rs.getAnalogInput("right")

    outputCall()

    if inject == 1 then delay = delay + 1 end
    if delay >= 280 then inject, delay = 0, 0 end

    if speed == 0 then
        shift("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        if batt <= 30 and inject == 0 then
            fuelFeed("bottom", "Engaged", "ddddddd")
            inject = 1
        elseif batt >= 35 then
            fuelFeed("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        end
    elseif speed <= 8 then
        shift("top", "Low RPM", "1111111")
        if batt >= 35 then
            fuelFeed("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        end
    else
        shift("left", "Engaged", "ddddddd")
        if batt >= 35 then
            fuelFeed("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        end
    end
end

title: unicoder.vbs
content:
'Unicoder v1.0.1, 2025-10-26.
'https://www.reddit.com/user/jcunews1
'https://pastebin.com/u/jcunews
'https://greasyfork.org/en/users/85671-jcunews
'
'Convert text with source character set to Unicode.
'A tool to help displaying CJK text when system codepage is not set to CJK.
'For use in console only.

sub help
  wsh.stdout.writeline "Usage: unicoder [/u] {charset} [input file]" _
    & vbcrlf & "If not input file is specified, use standard input." _
    & vbcrlf & "Use /u switch for UTF-8 output (for redirected output)."
  wsh.quit 1
end sub

if wsh.arguments.unnamed.count = 0 then help
set ds = createobject("adodb.stream") : ds.open
on error resume next
cs = wsh.arguments.unnamed(0)
ds.charset = cs
if err.number <> 0 then
  wsh.stdout.writeline "Invalid charset."
  wsh.quit 2
end if
on error goto 0
if wsh.arguments.unnamed.count >= 2 then
  ds.loadfromfile wsh.arguments.unnamed(1)
  ds.position = 0
  s = ""
  do while not ds.eos
    s = s & ds.readtext(1)
  loop
  wsh.stdout.write s
  wsh.quit
else
  ds.charset = "x-user-defined"
  ds.writetext wsh.stdin.readall
  ds.position = 0
  ds.charset = cs
end if
s = ""
do while not ds.eos
  s = s & ds.readtext(1)
loop
if wsh.arguments.named.exists("u") then
  set d = createobject("htmlfile")
  d.open
  d.write "<meta charset=utf-8><body><script id=z type=z>" & s & _
    "</script><script language=jscript>" & _
    "document.s=unescape(encodeURI(z.text))</script>"
  d.close
  s = d.s
  on error resume next
  for i = 1 to len(s)
    c = mid(s, i, 1)
    err.number = 0
    wsh.stdout.write c
    if err.number <> 0 then wsh.stdout.write chr(ascw(c))
  next
else
  wsh.stdout.write s
end if

title: Test Charcoal Tree Farm
content:
local function turn_around()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.turnLeft()
end

local function forward(times)
    for i = 1, times do
        turtle.forward()
    end
end

local function back(times)
    for i = 1, times do
        turtle.back()
    end
end

local function up(times)
    for i = 1, times do
        turtle.up()
    end
end

local function down(times)
    for i = 1, times do
        turtle.down()
    end
end

local function place_charcoal()
    for i = 1, 14 do
        local itDetail = turtle.getItemDetail(i)
        if itDetail and itDetail.name == 'minecraft:charcoal' then
            turtle.select(i)
            turtle.drop()
        end
    end
end

function create_charcoal()
    -- pace wood into furnace
    up(2)
    turtle.forward()
    for i = 1, 14 do
        local itDetail = turtle.getItemDetail(i)
        if itDetail and itDetail.name == 'minecraft:dark_oak_log' then
            turtle.select(i)
            turtle.dropDown()
        end
    end
    turtle.back()
    down(2)
    turtle.forward()
    turtle.suckUp()
    turtle.turnLeft()
    turtle.back()
    turtle.up()
    place_charcoal()
    turtle.down()
    turn_around()
    place_charcoal()

    -- place haul into chest
    turn_around()
    turtle.forward()
    for i = 1, 14 do
        turtle.select(i)
        turtle.drop()
    end
    turtle.turnLeft()
end

create_charcoal()

clubs <- read_csv(clubs_file, show_col_types = FALSE)

# --- ÎšÎ±Î¸Î±ÏÎ¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚ ÎºÎ±Î¹ ÎµÎ½Î±ÏÎ¼ÏŒÎ½Î¹ÏƒÎ· Clubs ---
colnames(clubs) <- tolower(trimws(colnames(clubs)))
club_name_source <- if("club_name" %in% colnames(clubs)) "club_name" else "club_id"
if("clubname" %in% colnames(clubs) & !("club_name" %in% colnames(clubs))) {
  club_name_source <- "clubname"
}

if("hours_per_week" %in% colnames(clubs)) {
  clubs <- clubs |> rename(hours = hours_per_week)
} else if(!("hours" %in% colnames(clubs))) {
  hours_col_name <- setdiff(colnames(clubs), c("club_id", "club_name", "clubname"))[1]
  if (!is.na(hours_col_name)) {
    clubs <- clubs |> rename(hours = hours_col_name)
  }
}

clubs <- clubs |>
  mutate(
    club_id = trimws(tolower(club_id)),
    club_name = .data[[club_name_source]], 
    club_name = trimws(club_name),
    hours = as.integer(hours),
    hours = if_else(is.na(hours), 2L, hours) 
  ) |>
  select(club_id, club_name, hours)

# --- ÎšÎ±Î¸Î±ÏÎ¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚ ÎºÎ±Î¹ ÎµÎ½Î±ÏÎ¼ÏŒÎ½Î¹ÏƒÎ· Responses ---
student_col <- colnames(responses)[1]
responses <- responses |>
  mutate(across(all_of(student_col), as.character)) 

initial_club_cols <- trimws(tolower(colnames(responses)[-1]))
colnames(responses) <- c(student_col, initial_club_cols)

responses_long_master <- responses |>
  pivot_longer(cols = -all_of(student_col),
               names_to = "ClubID", values_to = "Rank") |>
  mutate(
    ClubID = trimws(tolower(ClubID)),
    Rank = as.integer(Rank)
  ) |>
  filter(!is.na(Rank))

# --- Î•Î½ÎµÏÎ³Î­Ï‚ ÎšÎ±Ï„Î±ÏƒÏ„Î¬ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚ ---
active_clubs <- initial_club_cols
student_hours <- data.frame(StudentID = unique(responses[[student_col]]),
                            HoursAssigned = 0L,
                            stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
colnames(student_hours)[1] <- student_col
club_assignments <- data.frame(StudentID = character(), ClubID = character(), ClubName = character(), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
colnames(club_assignments)[1] <- student_col
round <- 1L

cat(sprintf("--- ÎˆÎ½Î±ÏÎ¾Î· Î”Î¹Î±Î´Î¹ÎºÎ±ÏƒÎ¯Î±Ï‚ ÎšÎ±Ï„Î±Î½Î¿Î¼Î®Ï‚ ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Ï‰Î½ (Î£Ï„ÏŒÏ‡Î¿Ï‚: %d ÎÏÎµÏ‚/ÎœÎ±Î¸Î·Ï„Î®, Min Pool: %d) ---\n", required_hours, min_pool_size))

repeat {
  # --- 1. Î¥Ï€Î¿Î»Î¿Î³Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚ Î ÏÏŽÏ„Ï‰Î½ Î ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÏ‰Î½ (Î¤ÏÎ­Ï‡Î¿Ï…ÏƒÎ± ÎºÎ±Ï„Î¬ÏƒÏ„Î±ÏƒÎ·) ---
  
  active_students <- student_hours |>
    filter(HoursAssigned < required_hours) |>
    pull(all_of(student_col))
  
  current_prefs <- responses_long_master |>
    filter(ClubID %in% active_clubs) |>
    filter(get(student_col) %in% active_students) |>
    group_by(across(all_of(student_col))) |>
    filter(Rank == min(Rank, na.rm = TRUE)) |> 
    ungroup()
  
  counts <- current_prefs |>
    count(ClubID, name = "FirstPrefCount") |>
    right_join(data.frame(ClubID = active_clubs), by = "ClubID") |>
    replace_na(list(FirstPrefCount = 0))
  
  cat(sprintf("\n*** Î“ÏÏÎ¿Ï‚ %d ***\n", round))
  
  # ÎˆÎ»ÎµÎ³Ï‡Î¿Ï‚ Î¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼Î¿Ï
  if(length(active_clubs) == 0 || length(active_students) == 0) {
    students_not_reached_target <- student_hours |>
      filter(HoursAssigned < required_hours)
    
    if(length(active_clubs) == 0 && nrow(students_not_reached_target) > 0) {
      cat(sprintf("\nÎ¤Î•Î¡ÎœÎ‘Î¤Î™Î£ÎœÎŸÎ£ Î›ÎŸÎ“Î© Î•ÎžÎ‘ÎÎ¤Î›Î—Î£Î—Î£ ÎŸÎœÎ™Î›Î©Î: %d Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚ Î´ÎµÎ½ ÏƒÏ…Î¼Ï€Î»Î®ÏÏ‰ÏƒÎ±Î½ Ï„Î¹Ï‚ %d ÏŽÏÎµÏ‚.\n", 
                  nrow(students_not_reached_target), required_hours))
    } else {
      cat("\nÎ¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚: ÎŒÎ»Î¿Î¹ Î¿Î¹ Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚ Î­Ï‡Î¿Ï…Î½ ÏƒÏ…Î¼Ï€Î»Î·ÏÏŽÏƒÎµÎ¹ Ï„Î¹Ï‚ ÏŽÏÎµÏ‚ Ï„Î¿Ï…Ï‚.\n")
    }
    break
  }
  
  # --- 2. Î•Î½Ï„Î¿Ï€Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚ Î”Î·Î¼Î¿Ï†Î¹Î»Î­ÏƒÏ„ÎµÏÎ¿Ï… ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Î¿Ï… ---
  max_count <- max(counts$FirstPrefCount)
  if (max_count == 0) {
    cat("Î”ÎµÎ½ Ï…Ï€Î¬ÏÏ‡Î¿Ï…Î½ Ï€Î»Î­Î¿Î½ Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚ Î³Î¹Î± ÎµÎ½ÎµÏÎ³Î¿ÏÏ‚ ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Î¿Ï…Ï‚. Î¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚.\n")
    break
  }
  
  pop_candidates <- counts |> filter(FirstPrefCount == max_count)
  club_to_select <- sort(pop_candidates$ClubID)[1]
  
  match_idx <- match(club_to_select, clubs$club_id)
  club_name <- clubs$club_name[match_idx]
  club_hours <- clubs$hours[match_idx] 
  
  cat(sprintf("-> Î”Î·Î¼Î¿Ï†Î¹Î»Î­ÏƒÏ„ÎµÏÎ¿Ï‚ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Ï‚: %s (%s) Î¼Îµ %d **Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚** Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚ (ÎÏÎµÏ‚: %d).\n",
              club_to_select, club_name, max_count, club_hours))
  
  # --- 3. Î”Î¹ÎµÏÏÏ…Î½ÏƒÎ· Pool Î¥Ï€Î¿ÏˆÎ·Ï†Î¯Ï‰Î½ (Î›ÎŸÎ“Î™ÎšÎ— Î•Î›Î‘Î§Î™Î£Î¤ÎŸÎ¥ 15) ---
  
  students_for_club_pool <- current_prefs |>
    filter(ClubID == club_to_select) |>
    pull(all_of(student_col))
  
  if(length(students_for_club_pool) < min_pool_size) {
    cat(sprintf("-> ÎŸÎ¹ Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚ (%d) ÎµÎ¯Î½Î±Î¹ < %d. Î‘Î½Î±Î¶Î®Ï„Î·ÏƒÎ· ÏƒÎµ Ï‡Î±Î¼Î·Î»ÏŒÏ„ÎµÏÎ± ranks...\n", 
                length(students_for_club_pool), min_pool_size))
    
    club_rankings <- responses_long_master |>
      filter(ClubID == club_to_select) |>
      filter(get(student_col) %in% active_students) |>
      arrange(Rank) |>
      select(all_of(student_col), Rank)
    
    max_rank_to_include <- club_rankings$Rank[min(nrow(club_rankings), min_pool_size)]
    
    students_for_club_pool <- club_rankings |>
      filter(Rank <= max_rank_to_include) |>
      pull(all_of(student_col))
    
    cat(sprintf("-> Î¤Î¿ pool Î´Î¹ÎµÏ…ÏÏÎ½Î¸Î·ÎºÎµ Î³Î¹Î± Î½Î± ÏƒÏ…Î¼Ï€ÎµÏÎ¹Î»Î¬Î²ÎµÎ¹ Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚ Î¼Î­Ï‡ÏÎ¹ Ï„Î·Î½ %dÎ· Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¯Î¼Î·ÏƒÎ· (Î£Ï…Î½Î¿Î»Î¹ÎºÎ¬: %d Ï…Ï€Î¿ÏˆÎ®Ï†Î¹Î¿Î¹).\n", 
                max_rank_to_include, length(students_for_club_pool)))
  }
  
  # --- 4. Î‘Ï…Ï„ÏŒÎ¼Î±Ï„Î· Î•Ï€Î¹Î»Î¿Î³Î® 15 ÎœÎ±Î¸Î·Ï„ÏŽÎ½ (Î ÏÎ¿ÏƒÎ¿Î¼Î¿Î¯Ï‰ÏƒÎ·) ---
  
  if (length(students_for_club_pool) > 0) {
    num_to_select <- min(auto_select_count, length(students_for_club_pool))
    final_selected_students <- sample(students_for_club_pool, size = num_to_select, replace = FALSE)
    
    cat(sprintf("-> Î•Ï€Î¹Î»Î­Î³Î¿Î½Ï„Î±Î¹ Ï„Ï…Ï‡Î±Î¯Î± %d Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚ Î±Ï€ÏŒ Ï„Î¿ pool.\n", num_to_select))
  } else {
    final_selected_students <- character(0)
  }
  
  
  # --- 5. ÎšÎ±Ï„Î±Ï‡ÏŽÏÎ·ÏƒÎ· ÎºÎ±Î¹ ÎœÎµÏ„Î±Ï†Î¿ÏÎ¬ Î¨Î®Ï†Ï‰Î½ ---
  
  if(length(final_selected_students) > 0) {
    new_assignments <- data.frame(StudentID = final_selected_students,
                                  ClubID = club_to_select,
                                  ClubName = club_name,
                                  stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    colnames(new_assignments)[1] <- student_col
    club_assignments <- bind_rows(club_assignments, new_assignments)
    
    for (sid in final_selected_students) {
      student_hours[student_hours[[student_col]] == sid, "HoursAssigned"] <- 
        student_hours[student_hours[[student_col]] == sid, "HoursAssigned"] + club_hours
    }
    
    cat(sprintf("-> ÎšÎ±Ï„Î±Ï‡Ï‰ÏÎ®Î¸Î·ÎºÎ±Î½ %d Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚ ÏƒÏ„Î¿Î½ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿ %s.\n", length(final_selected_students), club_name))
    
    assignment_file <- sprintf("%s_%s.csv", output_prefix_assignments, club_to_select)
    write_csv(new_assignments, assignment_file)
  }
  
  # Î‘Ï†Î±Î¯ÏÎµÏƒÎ· Ï„Î¿Ï… ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Î¿Ï… Î±Ï€ÏŒ Ï„Î· Î»Î¯ÏƒÏ„Î± Ï„Ï‰Î½ ÎµÎ½ÎµÏÎ³ÏŽÎ½ (Î’Î¬ÏƒÎµÎ¹ Ï„Î¿Ï… ÎšÎ±Î½ÏŒÎ½Î± Ï„Î¿Ï… Î§ÏÎ®ÏƒÏ„Î·)
  active_clubs <- setdiff(active_clubs, club_to_select)
  
  # --- 6. Î•Î½Î·Î¼Î­ÏÏ‰ÏƒÎ· Ranks (ÎœÎµÏ„Î±Ï†Î¿ÏÎ¬ Î¨Î®Ï†Ï‰Î½) ---
  
  responses_long_master <- responses_long_master |>
    mutate(Rank = ifelse(ClubID == club_to_select, NA_integer_, Rank)) |>
    filter(!is.na(Rank))
  
  responses_long_master <- responses_long_master |>
    group_by(across(all_of(student_col))) |>
    mutate(Rank = rank(Rank, ties.method = "min")) |> 
    ungroup()
  
  # --- 7. Î‘Ï€Î¿Î¸Î®ÎºÎµÏ…ÏƒÎ· Î•Î½Î´Î¹Î¬Î¼ÎµÏƒÏ‰Î½ Î‘ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Ï‰Î½ ---
  write_csv(student_hours, "student_hours_log.csv")
  
  round <- round + 1L
}

# --- Î¤ÎµÎ»Î¹ÎºÎ® ÎšÎ±Ï„Î±Î³ÏÎ±Ï†Î® & ÎÎ­Î¿ Î‘ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Î¿ (Student Club List) ---
cat("\nÎŸÎ»Î¿ÎºÎ»Î·ÏÏŽÎ¸Î·ÎºÎµ Î· Î´Î¹Î±Î´Î¹ÎºÎ±ÏƒÎ¯Î± ÎºÎ±Ï„Î±Î½Î¿Î¼Î®Ï‚.\n")
write_csv(club_assignments, "club_assignments_final.csv")


# --- Î’Î—ÎœÎ‘ 8: Î”Î—ÎœÎ™ÎŸÎ¥Î¡Î“Î™Î‘ Î‘Î¡Î§Î•Î™ÎŸÎ¥ ÎœÎ• Î›Î™Î£Î¤Î‘ ÎŸÎœÎ™Î›Î©Î Î‘ÎÎ‘ ÎœÎ‘Î˜Î—Î¤Î— ---

student_club_list <- club_assignments |>
  # ÎŸÎ¼Î±Î´Î¿Ï€Î¿Î¯Î·ÏƒÎ· Î±Î½Î¬ Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î®
  group_by(across(all_of(student_col))) |>
  # Î£Ï…Î½Î­Î½Ï‰ÏƒÎ· Ï„Ï‰Î½ ClubName ÏƒÎµ Î¼Î¯Î± ÏƒÏ…Î¼Î²Î¿Î»Î¿ÏƒÎµÎ¹ÏÎ¬, Ï‡Ï‰ÏÎ¹ÏƒÎ¼Î­Î½Î· Î¼Îµ ÎºÏŒÎ¼Î¼Î±
  summarise(
    Clubs_Assigned = paste(ClubName, collapse = ", "),
    .groups = 'drop'
  )

# Î•Î½ÏƒÏ‰Î¼Î¬Ï„Ï‰ÏƒÎ· Ï„Ï‰Î½ ÏƒÏ…Î½Î¿Î»Î¹ÎºÏŽÎ½ Ï‰ÏÏŽÎ½ Î³Î¹Î± Ï€Î»Î·ÏÎ­ÏƒÏ„ÎµÏÎ· ÎµÎ¹ÎºÏŒÎ½Î±
student_club_list <- student_club_list |>
  left_join(student_hours, by = student_col) |>
  select(all_of(student_col), Clubs_Assigned, HoursAssigned)

# Î‘Ï€Î¿Î¸Î®ÎºÎµÏ…ÏƒÎ· Ï„Î¿Ï… Î½Î­Î¿Ï… Î±ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Î¿Ï…
write_csv(student_club_list, "student_club_list.csv")
cat("Î”Î·Î¼Î¹Î¿Ï…ÏÎ³Î®Î¸Î·ÎºÎµ Ï„Î¿ Î±ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Î¿: student_club_list.csv (Î›Î¯ÏƒÏ„Î± ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Ï‰Î½ Î±Î½Î¬ ÎœÎ±Î¸Î·Ï„Î®)\n")

# --- Î’Î—ÎœÎ‘ 9: Î•Î¥Î¡Î•Î£Î— ÎŸÎœÎ™Î›Î©Î ÎœÎ• Î›Î™Î“ÎŸÎ¤Î•Î¡ÎŸÎ¥Î£ Î‘Î ÎŸ 10 ÎœÎ‘Î˜Î—Î¤Î•Î£ ---

# Î¥Ï€Î¿Î»Î¿Î³Î¯Î¶Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Ï„Î¿Ï…Ï‚ Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚ Î±Î½Î¬ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿
clubs_less_than_10 <- club_assignments |>
  # ÎŸÎ¼Î±Î´Î¿Ï€Î¿Î¯Î·ÏƒÎ· Î±Î½Î¬ ÏŒÎ½Î¿Î¼Î± ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Î¿Ï…
  group_by(ClubName) |>
  # ÎšÎ±Ï„Î±Î¼Î­Ï„ÏÎ·ÏƒÎ· Ï„Ï‰Î½ Î±Î½Î±Î¸Î­ÏƒÎµÏ‰Î½ (Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„ÏŽÎ½)
  summarise(
    Students_Count = n(),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) |>
  # Î¦Î¹Î»Ï„ÏÎ¬ÏÎ¹ÏƒÎ¼Î± Î¼ÏŒÎ½Î¿ Î³Î¹Î± ÏŒÏƒÎ¿Ï…Ï‚ Î­Ï‡Î¿Ï…Î½ Î»Î¹Î³ÏŒÏ„ÎµÏÎ¿Ï…Ï‚ Î±Ï€ÏŒ 10 Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î­Ï‚
  filter(Students_Count < 10) |>
  # Î¤Î±Î¾Î¹Î½ÏŒÎ¼Î·ÏƒÎ· Î³Î¹Î± ÎµÏ…ÎºÎ¿Î»ÏŒÏ„ÎµÏÎ· ÎµÏ€Î¹ÏƒÎºÏŒÏ€Î·ÏƒÎ·
  arrange(Students_Count, ClubName)

# Î•ÎºÏ„ÏÏ€Ï‰ÏƒÎ· Î±Ï€Î¿Ï„ÎµÎ»ÎµÏƒÎ¼Î¬Ï„Ï‰Î½ ÏƒÏ„Î·Î½ ÎºÎ¿Î½ÏƒÏŒÎ»Î±
cat("\n\n--- ÎŸÎœÎ™Î›ÎŸÎ™ ÎœÎ• Î›Î™Î“ÎŸÎ¤Î•Î¡ÎŸÎ¥Î£ Î‘Î ÎŸ 10 ÎœÎ‘Î˜Î—Î¤Î•Î£ ---\n")
print(clubs_less_than_10)

# Î‘Ï€Î¿Î¸Î®ÎºÎµÏ…ÏƒÎ· Ï„Î¿Ï… Î±Ï€Î¿Ï„ÎµÎ»Î­ÏƒÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¿Ï‚ ÏƒÎµ Î±ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Î¿ CSV
write_csv(clubs_less_than_10, "clubs_less_than_10_students.csv")
cat("\nÎ‘Ï€Î¿Î¸Î·ÎºÎµÏÏ„Î·ÎºÎ±Î½ Ï„Î± Î±Ï€Î¿Ï„ÎµÎ»Î­ÏƒÎ¼Î±Ï„Î± ÏƒÏ„Î¿: clubs_less_than_10_students.csv\n")

title: Debounced Button rev_01
Eliminate Clubs
content:
# eliminateclubs_fixed.R
# Î•Î¾Î¬ÏÏ„Î·ÏƒÎ·: install.packages(c("dplyr", "readr", "tidyr"))

library(dplyr)
library(readr)
library(tidyr)

# --- Î¡Ï…Î¸Î¼Î¯ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚ ---
min_threshold <- 10L
responses_file <- "responses.csv"
clubs_file <- "clubs.csv"
output_prefix <- "responses_round"

# --- Î”Î¹Î±Î²Î¬Î¶Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Î´ÎµÎ´Î¿Î¼Î­Î½Î± ---
responses <- read_csv(responses_file, show_col_types = FALSE)
clubs <- read_csv(clubs_file, show_col_types = FALSE)

# --- ÎšÎ±Î¸Î±ÏÎ¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚ ÎºÎ±Î¹ ÎµÎ½Î±ÏÎ¼ÏŒÎ½Î¹ÏƒÎ· (ÏŒÏ€Ï‰Ï‚ Ï€ÏÎ¹Î½) ---
colnames(clubs) <- tolower(trimws(colnames(clubs)))
clubs$club_id <- trimws(tolower(clubs$club_id))
if("club_name" %in% colnames(clubs)) {
  clubs$club_name <- trimws(clubs$club_name)
} else if("clubname" %in% colnames(clubs)) {
  clubs$club_name <- trimws(clubs$clubname)
} else {
  clubs$club_name <- clubs$club_id
}

student_col <- colnames(responses)[1]
initial_club_cols <- trimws(tolower(colnames(responses)[-1]))
colnames(responses) <- c(student_col, initial_club_cols)

# ÎœÎµÏ„Î±Ï„ÏÎ¿Ï€Î® ÏƒÎµ 'long' Î¼Î¿ÏÏ†Î® Î³Î¹Î± ÎµÏ…ÎºÎ¿Î»ÏŒÏ„ÎµÏÎ· Î´Î¹Î±Ï‡ÎµÎ¯ÏÎ¹ÏƒÎ· Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÏ‰Î½
responses_long_master <- responses |>
  pivot_longer(cols = -all_of(student_col),
               names_to = "ClubID", values_to = "Rank") |>
  mutate(
    ClubID = trimws(tolower(ClubID)),
    # Î•Î¾Î±ÏƒÏ†Î¬Î»Î¹ÏƒÎ· ÏŒÏ„Î¹ Ï„Î¿ Rank ÎµÎ¯Î½Î±Î¹ Î±ÎºÎ­ÏÎ±Î¹Î¿Ï‚
    Rank = as.integer(Rank)
  ) |>
  # Î¦Î¹Î»Ï„ÏÎ¬ÏÎ¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Î¼ÏŒÎ½Î¿ Ï„Î¹Ï‚ ÎºÎ±Ï„Î±Î³ÎµÎ³ÏÎ±Î¼Î¼Î­Î½ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚
  filter(!is.na(Rank))


round <- 1L
elimination_log <- data.frame(Round=integer(), ClubID=character(), ClubName=character(), FirstPrefCount=integer(), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
active_clubs <- initial_club_cols

repeat {
  # --- Î’Î®Î¼Î± 1: Î¥Ï€Î¿Î»Î¿Î³Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚ Î ÏÏŽÏ„Ï‰Î½ Î ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÏ‰Î½ (Î¤ÏÎ­Ï‡Î¿Ï…ÏƒÎ± ÎºÎ±Ï„Î¬ÏƒÏ„Î±ÏƒÎ·) ---
  # Î’ÏÎ¯ÏƒÎºÎ¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Ï„Î·Î½ Ï„ÏÎ­Ï‡Î¿Ï…ÏƒÎ± Ï…ÏˆÎ·Î»ÏŒÏ„ÎµÏÎ· Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¯Î¼Î·ÏƒÎ· (Ï„Î¿ Ï‡Î±Î¼Î·Î»ÏŒÏ„ÎµÏÎ¿ Rank) Î³Î¹Î± ÎºÎ¬Î¸Îµ Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î®
  current_prefs <- responses_long_master |>
    # Î¦Î¹Î»Ï„ÏÎ¬ÏÎ¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Î¼ÏŒÎ½Î¿ Ï„Î¿Ï…Ï‚ ÎµÎ½ÎµÏÎ³Î¿ÏÏ‚ ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Î¿Ï…Ï‚
    filter(ClubID %in% active_clubs) |>
    # Î’ÏÎ¯ÏƒÎºÎ¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Ï„Î¿ ÎµÎ»Î¬Ï‡Î¹ÏƒÏ„Î¿ Rank (Ï„Î·Î½ Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„Î· Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¯Î¼Î·ÏƒÎ·)
    group_by(across(all_of(student_col))) |>
    filter(Rank == min(Rank, na.rm = TRUE)) |>
    ungroup()
  
  # ÎœÎµÏ„ÏÎ¬Î¼Îµ Ï„Î¹Ï‚ Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚
  counts <- current_prefs |>
    count(ClubID, name = "FirstPrefCount") |>
    right_join(data.frame(ClubID = active_clubs), by = "ClubID") |>
    replace_na(list(FirstPrefCount = 0)) |>
    # ÎœÎµÏ„Î±Ï„ÏÎ¿Ï€Î® ÏƒÎµ named vector Î³Î¹Î± ÎµÏÎºÎ¿Î»Î· Ï‡ÏÎ®ÏƒÎ·
    tibble::deframe()
  
  cat(sprintf("\n--- Î“ÏÏÎ¿Ï‚ %d ---\n", round))
  cat("ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Î¹ ÎºÎ±Î¹ Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚:\n")
  print(data.frame(ClubID=names(counts), FirstPref=as.integer(counts)), row.names = FALSE)
  
  # --- Î’Î®Î¼Î± 2: ÎˆÎ»ÎµÎ³Ï‡Î¿Ï‚ Î¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼Î¿Ï ---
  if(length(active_clubs) == 0) {
    cat("\nÎ¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚: Î”ÎµÎ½ Î­Î¼ÎµÎ¹Î½Îµ ÎºÎ±Î½Î­Î½Î±Ï‚ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Ï‚.\n")
    break
  }
  if(all(counts >= min_threshold)) {
    cat("\nÎ¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚: ÏŒÎ»Î¿Î¹ Î¿Î¹ ÎµÎ½ÎµÏÎ³Î¿Î¯ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Î¹ Î­Ï‡Î¿Ï…Î½ Ï„Î¿Ï…Î»Î¬Ï‡Î¹ÏƒÏ„Î¿Î½ ", min_threshold, " Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚.\n", sep = "")
    # Î‘Î½Î±Î´Î·Î¼Î¹Î¿Ï…ÏÎ³Î¯Î± Ï„Î¿Ï… Ï„ÎµÎ»Î¹ÎºÎ¿Ï responses_wide Î³Î¹Î± Î±Ï€Î¿Î¸Î®ÎºÎµÏ…ÏƒÎ·
    responses_final_wide <- responses_long_master |>
      filter(ClubID %in% active_clubs) |>
      pivot_wider(id_cols = all_of(student_col),
                  names_from = ClubID, values_from = Rank)
    
    write_csv(responses_final_wide, "responses_final.csv")
    break
  }
  
  # --- Î’Î®Î¼Î± 3: Î•Î¾Î¬Î»ÎµÎ¹ÏˆÎ· ---
  counts_df <- data.frame(ClubID=names(counts), FirstPrefCount=as.integer(counts)) |>
    filter(FirstPrefCount < min_threshold)
  
  if(nrow(counts_df) == 0) {
    # Î‘Ï…Ï„ÏŒ Î´ÎµÎ½ Î¸Î± Î­Ï€ÏÎµÏ€Îµ Î½Î± ÏƒÏ…Î¼Î²ÎµÎ¯ Î»ÏŒÎ³Ï‰ Ï„Î¿Ï… Ï€ÏÎ¿Î·Î³Î¿ÏÎ¼ÎµÎ½Î¿Ï… ÎµÎ»Î­Î³Ï‡Î¿Ï…,
    # Î±Î»Î»Î¬ ÎµÎ¾Î±ÏƒÏ†Î±Î»Î¯Î¶ÎµÎ¹ Ï„Î· ÏƒÏ…Î½Î­Ï‡ÎµÎ¹Î± Î±Î½ Ï„Î¿ all(counts >= min_threshold) Î´ÎµÎ½ Ï€Î¹Î¬ÏƒÎµÎ¹ Ï„Î·Î½ Ï€ÎµÏÎ¯Ï€Ï„Ï‰ÏƒÎ·.
    cat("\nÎ¤ÎµÏÎ¼Î±Ï„Î¹ÏƒÎ¼ÏŒÏ‚: ÎŒÎ»Î¿Î¹ Î¿Î¹ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Î¹ Î¬Î½Ï‰ Ï„Î¿Ï… Î¿ÏÎ¯Î¿Ï….\n")
    next 
  }
  
  min_count <- min(counts_df$FirstPrefCount)
  elim_candidates <- counts_df |> filter(FirstPrefCount == min_count)
  
  # Î›Î¿Î³Î¹ÎºÎ® Î™ÏƒÎ¿Ï€Î±Î»Î¯Î±Ï‚: ÎµÏ€Î¹Î»Î­Î³Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Î±Î»Ï†Î±Î²Î·Ï„Î¹ÎºÎ¬
  club_to_elim <- sort(elim_candidates$ClubID)[1]
  
  match_idx <- match(club_to_elim, clubs$club_id)
  club_name <- if(!is.na(match_idx)) clubs$club_name[match_idx] else club_to_elim
  cat(sprintf("Î•Î¾Î±Î»ÎµÎ¯Ï†ÎµÏ„Î±Î¹ Î¿ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Ï‚: %s (%s) Î¼Îµ %d Ï€ÏÏŽÏ„ÎµÏ‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚.\n",
              club_to_elim, club_name, min_count))
  
  elimination_log <- rbind(elimination_log,
                           data.frame(Round=round,
                                      ClubID=club_to_elim,
                                      ClubName=club_name,
                                      FirstPrefCount=min_count,
                                      stringsAsFactors = FALSE))
  
  # --- Î’Î®Î¼Î± 4: ÎœÎµÏ„Î±Ï†Î¿ÏÎ¬ Î¨Î®Ï†Ï‰Î½ (Î‘Î½Î±Î²Î¬Î¸Î¼Î¹ÏƒÎ· Î ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÏ‰Î½) ---
  
  # 1. Î‘Ï€ÎµÎ½ÎµÏÎ³Î¿Ï€Î¿Î¯Î·ÏƒÎ· Ï„Î¿Ï… ÎµÎ¾Î±Î»ÎµÎ¹Ï†Î¸Î­Î½Ï„Î¿Ï‚ ÎŸÎ¼Î¯Î»Î¿Ï…
  active_clubs <- setdiff(active_clubs, club_to_elim)
  
  # 2. Î‘ÎºÏÏÏ‰ÏƒÎ· Ï„Î¿Ï… club_to_elim (Î¸Î­Ï„Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Ï„Î¿ Rank Ï„Î¿Ï… ÏƒÎµ NA)
  responses_long_master <- responses_long_master |>
    mutate(Rank = ifelse(ClubID == club_to_elim, NA_integer_, Rank)) |>
    # Î‘Ï†Î±Î¹ÏÎ¿ÏÎ¼Îµ Ï€Î»Î­Î¿Î½ Ï„Î± NA rank, ÎºÎ±Î¸ÏŽÏ‚ Î¿ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Ï‚ Î´ÎµÎ½ Î¼ÎµÏ„ÏÎ¬ÎµÎ¹
    filter(!is.na(Rank))
  
  # 3. Î‘Î½Î±Î²Î±Î¸Î¼Î¯Î¶Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Ï„Î± Ranks Î³Î¹Î± ÎºÎ¬Î¸Îµ Î¼Î±Î¸Î·Ï„Î®
  responses_long_master <- responses_long_master |>
    group_by(across(all_of(student_col))) |>
    # Î‘Î½Î±Î²Î±Î¸Î¼Î¯Î¶Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Ï„Î± Ranks (1, 3, 4, 5... Î³Î¯Î½ÎµÏ„Î±Î¹ 1, 2, 3, 4...)
    # Î•Ï€Î±Î½Î±-Î±ÏÎ¹Î¸Î¼Î¿ÏÎ¼Îµ Ï„Î¹Ï‚ Ï€ÏÎ¿Ï„Î¹Î¼Î®ÏƒÎµÎ¹Ï‚ Î¼Îµ Î²Î¬ÏƒÎ· Ï„Î·Î½ Ï„ÏÎ­Ï‡Î¿Ï…ÏƒÎ± ÏƒÎµÎ¹ÏÎ¬ Ï„Î¿Ï…Ï‚
    mutate(Rank = rank(Rank, ties.method = "min")) |> 
    ungroup()
  
  # --- Î‘Ï€Î¿Î¸Î®ÎºÎµÏ…ÏƒÎ· Î•Î½Î´Î¹Î¬Î¼ÎµÏƒÎ¿Ï… Î‘ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Î¿Ï… (responses_wide) ---
  round_file <- sprintf("%s%d.csv", output_prefix, round)
  
  responses_round_wide <- responses_long_master |>
    pivot_wider(id_cols = all_of(student_col),
                names_from = ClubID, values_from = Rank) |>
    # Î£Ï…Î¼Ï€Î»Î·ÏÏŽÎ½Î¿Ï…Î¼Îµ Î¼Îµ NA Ï„Î¿Ï…Ï‚ ÎŒÎ¼Î¹Î»Î¿Ï…Ï‚ Ï€Î¿Ï… Î­Ï‡Î¿Ï…Î½ Î®Î´Î· ÎµÎ¾Î±Î»ÎµÎ¹Ï†Î¸ÎµÎ¯ (Î±Î½ Ï…Ï€Î¬ÏÏ‡Î¿Ï…Î½)
    select(all_of(student_col), all_of(active_clubs))
  
  write_csv(responses_round_wide, round_file)
  cat("Î‘Ï€Î¿Î¸Î·ÎºÎµÏÏ„Î·ÎºÎµ ÎµÎ½Î´Î¹Î¬Î¼ÎµÏƒÎ¿ Î±ÏÏ‡ÎµÎ¯Î¿: ", round_file, "\n")
  
  round <- round + 1L
}

if(nrow(elimination_log)>0) write_csv(elimination_log, "elimination_log.csv")
cat("\nÎŸÎ»Î¿ÎºÎ»Î·ÏÏŽÎ¸Î·ÎºÎµ Î· Î´Î¹Î±Î´Î¹ÎºÎ±ÏƒÎ¯Î± ÎµÎ¾Î¬Î»ÎµÎ¹ÏˆÎ·Ï‚. Î”ÎµÏ‚ Ï„Î¿ elimination_log.csv.\n")

title: reactorInfoClient
content:
-- Reactor Info Client
-- Receives reactor statistics via rednet and displays them on monitor

-- Configuration
local PROTOCOL = "reactor_stats"
local TIMEOUT = 5  -- Seconds to wait for data before showing error

-- Initialize peripherals
local m = peripheral.wrap("monitor_1")
if not m then
    print("Error: No monitor found!")
    return
end

-- Open rednet on any available modem
local modem = nil
for _, side in ipairs(peripheral.getNames()) do
    if peripheral.getType(side) == "modem" then
        modem = peripheral.wrap(side)
        if modem.isWireless() then
            rednet.open(side)
            print("Rednet opened on wireless modem: " .. side)
            break
        end
    end
end

if not modem then
    print("Error: No wireless modem found!")
    return
end

-- Rainbow colors for border animation
local rainbow_colors = {colors.red, colors.orange, colors.yellow, colors.lime, colors.cyan, colors.blue, colors.purple, colors.magenta}

-- Function to draw progress bar
local function drawProgressBar(x, y, value, min_val, max_val, target, unit, bar_width, force_color, min_indicator)
  bar_width = bar_width or 20
  local percentage = math.max(0, math.min(100, ((value - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)) * 100))
  local filled_chars = math.floor((percentage / 100) * bar_width)
  
  -- Color coding based on proximity to target
  local color = colors.red
  if force_color then
    color = force_color
  elseif target then
    local target_percentage = ((target - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)) * 100
    local diff = math.abs(percentage - target_percentage)
    if diff < 10 then
      color = colors.lime
    elseif diff < 25 then
      color = colors.yellow
    end
  else
    -- Default color grading for values without targets
    if percentage > 66 then
      color = colors.lime
    elseif percentage > 33 then
      color = colors.yellow
    end
  end
  
  m.setCursorPos(x, y)
  m.setTextColor(colors.gray)
  m.write("[")
  
  -- Calculate minimum indicator position if provided
  local min_indicator_pos = nil
  if min_indicator then
    min_indicator_pos = math.floor(((min_indicator - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)) * bar_width)
  end
  
  -- Draw filled portion
  for i = 1, bar_width do
    if min_indicator_pos and i == min_indicator_pos then
      m.setTextColor(colors.cyan)
      m.write("|")
    elseif i <= filled_chars then
      m.setTextColor(color)
      m.write("=")
    else
      m.setTextColor(colors.gray)
      m.write("-")
    end
  end
  
  m.setTextColor(colors.gray)
  m.write("] ")
  m.setTextColor(colors.white)
  m.write(string.format("%.2f %s", value, unit))
end

-- Function to show startup animation
local function showStartupAnimation()
    local y_padding = 2
    local x_padding = 3
    local width, height = m.getSize()
    
    m.setTextScale(1)
    m.clear()
    
    -- Phase 2: Moving rainbow border with centered text
    local title_lines = {"Lag 4 President", "Draconic Reactor", "Quantum Monitor v1.0", " ~ By THCoder aka David"}
    local corner_text = "Kennst du eigentlich Andi? :D"
    
    for frame = 1, 25 do
      m.clear()
      
      -- Draw moving rainbow border
      local color_offset = frame % #rainbow_colors
      
      -- Top and bottom borders
      for x = 1, width do
        local color_index = ((x + color_offset - 1) % #rainbow_colors) + 1
        m.setTextColor(rainbow_colors[color_index])
        m.setCursorPos(x, 1)
        m.write("=")
        m.setCursorPos(x, height)
        m.write("=")
      end
      
      -- Left and right borders
      for y = 2, height - 1 do
        local color_index = ((y + color_offset - 1) % #rainbow_colors) + 1
        m.setTextColor(rainbow_colors[color_index])
        m.setCursorPos(1, y)
        m.write("|")
        m.setCursorPos(width, y)
        m.write("|")
      end
      
      -- Draw centered title text with rainbow colors
      local start_y = math.floor((height - #title_lines) / 2)
      for i, line in ipairs(title_lines) do
        local x_pos = math.floor((width - #line) / 2) + 1
        local line_color = rainbow_colors[((i - 1) % #rainbow_colors) + 1]
        
        if frame > i * 3 then
          for j = 1, math.min(#line, frame - i * 3) do
            m.setTextColor(line_color)
            m.setCursorPos(x_pos + j - 1, start_y + i)
            m.write(line:sub(j, j))
          end
        end
      end
      
      -- Draw corner text (bottom right)
      if frame > 15 then
        m.setTextColor(colors.cyan)
        m.setCursorPos(width - #corner_text - 2, height - 2)
        m.write(corner_text)
      end
      
      sleep(0.1)
    end
    
    sleep(3)
end

-- Function to display reactor data
local function displayReactorData(info)
    local y_padding = 2
    local x_padding = 3
    local value_align = 25
    local width, height = m.getSize()
    
    -- Clear and prepare monitor
    m.clear()
    m.setTextScale(1)
    
    -- Header line
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding + 8, 1)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("* ")
    m.setTextColor(colors.red)
    m.write("Lag4President")
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write(" - ")
    m.setTextColor(colors.purple)
    m.write("Draconic Reactor")
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write(" *")
    
    -- Extract data
    local status = info["status"]
    local temp = info["temperature"]
    local energyOut = info["generationRate"] / 1000 -- Convert to kRF/t
    local shieldIn = info["fieldDrainRate"] / 1000 -- Convert to kRF/t
    local netEnergy = energyOut - shieldIn
    local fieldStrength = (info["fieldStrength"] / info["maxFieldStrength"]) * 100
    local saturation = (info["energySaturation"] / info["maxEnergySaturation"]) * 100
    
    -- Check for fuel-related data
    local fuelConversion = info["fuelConversion"] or 0
    local maxFuelConversion = info["maxFuelConversion"] or 1
    local fuelConversionRate = info["fuelConversionRate"] or 0
    
    -- Calculate fuel percentage if available
    local fuelPercentage = 0
    if maxFuelConversion > 0 then
      fuelPercentage = (fuelConversion / maxFuelConversion) * 100
    end
    
    local row = y_padding + 1  -- Start below header
    
    -- Status (no progress bar)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Reactor Status:")
    m.setCursorPos(value_align, row)
    if status == "running" or status == "online" then
      m.setTextColor(colors.lime)
      m.write("Running")
    elseif status == "cooling" then
      m.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
      m.write("Shutting Down...")
    elseif status == "cold" then
      m.setTextColor(colors.red)
      m.write("Offline / Powered off")
    elseif status == "charging" then
      m.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
      m.write("Charging")
    elseif status == "charged" then
      m.setTextColor(colors.lime)
      m.write("Charged - Ready for Activation")
    else
      m.setTextColor(colors.gray)
      m.write("Unknown State")
    end
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Temperature progress bar (0-8000, with minimum indicator at 2000)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Temperature:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, temp, 0, 8000, 7500, "C", 15, nil, 2000)
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Energy Output progress bar with efficiency scaling
    local base_output = 4000
    local efficiency_multiplier = 1 + (fuelPercentage / 100) * 1.5
    local expected_output = base_output * efficiency_multiplier
    local max_output = base_output * 2.5
    
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Energy Output:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, energyOut, 0, max_output, expected_output, "kRF/t", 15)
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Field Input progress bar (0-2000, target 1400)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Field Input:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, shieldIn, 0, 2000, 1400, "kRF/t", 15)
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Net Energy (just value with color grading)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Net Energy:")
    m.setCursorPos(value_align, row)
    if netEnergy < 0 then
      m.setTextColor(colors.red)
    elseif netEnergy < 1000 then
      m.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
    else
      m.setTextColor(colors.lime)
    end
    m.write(string.format("%.2f kRF/t", netEnergy))
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Field Strength progress bar (0-100, target 15)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Field Strength:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, fieldStrength, 0, 100, 25, "%", 15)
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Energy Saturation progress bar (0-100, target 15)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Energy Saturation:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, saturation, 0, 100, 15, "%", 15)
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Fuel Conversion progress bar (0-100) - white color
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Fuel Progress:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, fuelPercentage, 0, 100, nil, "%", 15, colors.white)
    row = row + 2
    
    -- Fuel Rate progress bar (0-5)
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding, row)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("Fuel Rate:")
    drawProgressBar(value_align, row, fuelConversionRate / 1000, 0, 5, nil, "nb/t", 15)
    
    -- Bottom warning notes
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding + 5, height - 3)
    m.setTextColor(colors.red)
    m.write("NOTE:")
    m.setTextColor(colors.orange)
    m.write(" NEVER exceed 8000 C temperature!")
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding + 11, height - 2)
    m.write("NEVER let shield drop below 10%!")
    m.setCursorPos(x_padding + 11, height - 1)
    m.write("But making it close is quite rewarding :)")
end

-- Function to show connection error
local function showConnectionError()
    m.clear()
    m.setTextScale(1)
    
    local width, height = m.getSize()
    local y_center = math.floor(height / 2)
    
    m.setCursorPos(1, y_center - 2)
    m.setTextColor(colors.red)
    m.write("CONNECTION ERROR")
    
    m.setCursorPos(1, y_center)
    m.setTextColor(colors.white)
    m.write("No data received from server")
    
    m.setCursorPos(1, y_center + 1)
    m.write("Waiting for reactor server...")
    
    m.setCursorPos(1, y_center + 3)
    m.setTextColor(colors.gray)
    m.write("Protocol: " .. PROTOCOL)
end

-- Main program
print("Reactor Info Client Started")
print("Listening for protocol: " .. PROTOCOL)
print("Press Ctrl+T to stop")

-- Show startup animation
showStartupAnimation()

while true do
    -- Listen for reactor data
    local sender, message, protocol = rednet.receive(PROTOCOL, TIMEOUT)
    
    if sender and message and protocol == PROTOCOL then
        -- Display the received reactor data
        displayReactorData(message)
        
        -- Debug output to terminal
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        print("=== REACTOR CLIENT STATUS ===")
        print("Connected to server ID: " .. sender)
        print("Last update: " .. os.time())
        print("Reactor status: " .. tostring(message.status))
        print("")
        print("Displaying data on monitor...")
    else
        -- No data received within timeout
        showConnectionError()
        
        -- Debug output to terminal
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        print("=== REACTOR CLIENT ERROR ===")
        print("No data received within " .. TIMEOUT .. " seconds")
        print("Waiting for server...")
    end
end

title: reactorInfoServer
content:
-- Reactor Info Server
-- Reads reactor statistics and broadcasts them via rednet every 0.5 seconds

-- Configuration
local BROADCAST_INTERVAL = 0.5
local PROTOCOL = "reactor_stats"

-- Initialize peripherals
local r = peripheral.wrap("bottom")
if not r then
    print("Error: No reactor found on bottom!")
    return
end

-- Open rednet on any available modem
local modem = nil
for _, side in ipairs(peripheral.getNames()) do
    if peripheral.getType(side) == "modem" then
        modem = peripheral.wrap(side)
        if modem.isWireless() then
            rednet.open(side)
            print("Rednet opened on wireless modem: " .. side)
            break
        end
    end
end

if not modem then
    print("Error: No wireless modem found!")
    return
end

print("Reactor Info Server Started")
print("Broadcasting on protocol: " .. PROTOCOL)
print("Interval: " .. BROADCAST_INTERVAL .. " seconds")
print("Press Ctrl+T to stop")
print("")

while true do
    -- Get reactor information
    local success, info = pcall(function() return r.getReactorInfo() end)
    
    if success and info then
        -- Print statistics to local terminal
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        print("=== REACTOR SERVER STATUS ===")
        print("Status: " .. tostring(info.status))
        print("Temperature: " .. string.format("%.2f C", info.temperature))
        print("Generation: " .. string.format("%.2f kRF/t", info.generationRate / 1000))
        print("Field Drain: " .. string.format("%.2f kRF/t", info.fieldDrainRate / 1000))
        print("Net Energy: " .. string.format("%.2f kRF/t", (info.generationRate - info.fieldDrainRate) / 1000))
        print("Field Strength: " .. string.format("%.2f%%", (info.fieldStrength / info.maxFieldStrength) * 100))
        print("Energy Saturation: " .. string.format("%.2f%%", (info.energySaturation / info.maxEnergySaturation) * 100))
        
        -- Add fuel information if available
        if info.fuelConversion and info.maxFuelConversion then
            print("Fuel Progress: " .. string.format("%.2f%%", (info.fuelConversion / info.maxFuelConversion) * 100))
        end
        if info.fuelConversionRate then
            print("Fuel Rate: " .. string.format("%.3f nb/t", info.fuelConversionRate / 1000))
        end
        
        print("")
        print("Broadcasting to clients...")
        
        -- Broadcast the reactor info to all clients
        rednet.broadcast(info, PROTOCOL)
        
    else
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        print("=== REACTOR SERVER ERROR ===")
        print("Failed to read reactor data!")
        print("Error: " .. tostring(info))
        print("")
        print("Retrying in " .. BROADCAST_INTERVAL .. " seconds...")
    end
    
    sleep(BROADCAST_INTERVAL)
end
